commit_message:
Move dnsmasq-neutron.conf to /etc/neutron/dnsmasq

The default dnsmasq configuration file doesn't operate with the Kilo
agents in /etc/neutron when used with the --config-dir option.  Instead move
it to a subdirectory.

Change-Id: Iab8a54e879f8e630ba38205750ca9670e82834df
Partially-Implements: blueprint port-kilo

commit_message:
The Neutron agents need their configuration directory specified

Add a --config-dir specification to each agent run.

Change-Id: I0426caf2ca17185c0789753d4aa9637c5b4327ec
Partially-Implements: blueprint port-kilo

commit_message:
The neutron dockerfile needs an update for Kilo

policy.json comes from the openstack-neutron package and is required
for the agents to run.  So install it.  fwaas_driver.ini has been deleted
in master and in the kilo branch, but the agents won't run without the
file present.  So copy one from the Juno release.

fwaas_driver.ini is probably not actually required, but there is a
configuration problem somewhere in our Neutron code base.  We are out
of time for the Kilo branch, so this short term workaround should be fine.

Change-Id: I154599925308765349634b1a53e598599fc20ec1
Partially-Implements: blueprint port-kilo

commit_message:
Glance has some undefined dependencies in Kilo packaging

Glance has two undefined dependencies.  Without installing these
dependencies out of band, glance will not operate.

Change-Id: I096881467d8e0022d58e6c6f745e610d9332dd82
Partially-Implements: blueprint port-kilo

commit_message:
Make nova read config files for Kilo

In Kilo, nova no longer reads the config files automatically.  They must
be specified in the command line to run the nova-* tools.

Change-Id: Ifbdf4fd3f952f7bb65e9937b46cf9b96e262c3b0
Paritally-Impleents: blueprint port-kilo

I am concerned that configuring neutron in the {DEFAULT} section of nova.conf will go away in Kilo. Therefore, we will need to revert these changes to the original configuration.

I think we need to have a broader discussion on how we will go about supporting multiple openstack releases. For example, should we cut an Icehouse release and have this config change go in that branch?'}, {'account_id': 6836, 'date': '2015-04-21 21:17:08.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1 -Workflow'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-04-21 21:26:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Workflow-1

The changes that introduced the setting of these config options definitely should not be reverted.  nova compute is DOA without the predecessor to these changes in Juno.  These are mandatory configuration items.  Between Icehouse and Juno they were broken into separate sections.  Agree re broader discussion.'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-05-02 21:16:04.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review-2'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-05-06 13:06:37.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

Merge Failed.

This change was unable to be automatically merged with the current state of the repository. Please rebase your change and upload a new patchset.'}, {'account_id': 2834, 'date': '2015-05-06 20:52:18.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Change neutron configuration to work with i, j, k

The neutron configuration variables used in a previous version
of this patch work on Juno only.  They fail with Icehouse without
warning.  Instead just use variables that work on all three versions
of OpenStack.

Change-Id: I0d9c6e5a25510287c9da59164d5bc3f64815213d

commit_message:
Add a novnc container running the novnc-proxy.

All VNC-specific configuration bits are moved from nova-api-base to
nova-compute and the new nova-novncproxy and nova-consoleauth
containers. The compose specification has been updated to reflect this.

A future patch will make the desired backend configurable (spice/vnc).

Change-Id: I8b64abf125fd1ecd7d3463515e3717dd9bd60420
Blueprint: novnc-container

commit_message:
Clean Gemfile: drop rspec-puppet and rake

Both of rspec-puppet and rake get pulled in by puppetlabs_spec_helper
so there is no need to keep them in the Gemfile.

Change-Id: I6eec0cd69b34689db1b3adbe48cca43874cc7d9d

commit_message:
Fix exponentially growing AJAX updates for table rows

Schedule next table rows update only when the last row was
updated. Since unit-test for this fix relies on a blueprint
replace-qunit-tests-with-jasmine it is moved to a separate commit to
speed up this fix merge, see https://review.openstack.org/#/c/179013/

Closes-Bug: #1263665
(cherry picked from commit ca090378b4875afebdebd67bdb457eebad6b2b7d)

Conflict Resolution Notes:
cherry-pick needed to have the old body of the complete: function
manually removed - it wasn't sure if it still belonged (resulting in
nearly duplicate code) or should be removed. I'm a bit surprised the
cherry-pick didn't auto-resolve.

Conflicts:
	horizon/static/horizon/js/horizon.tables.js

Change-Id: Id603a4fde5713d8f2b85b1dcf72c82c93a87c755

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-04-28 23:08:59.000000000', 'message': 'Trait_* models have incorrect type for key

Each of the TraitText, TraintInt, TraitFloat
and TraitDatetime have key column which has
its type defined incorrectly as Integer. The
migrate script correctly defines the type as
String(255).

This fix updates the sqlalchemy Trait* models

commit_message:
Trait_* models have incorrect type for key

Each of the TraitText, TraintInt, TraitFloat
and TraitDatetime have key column which has
its type defined incorrectly as Integer. The
migrate script correctly defines the type as
String(255).

This fix updates the sqlalchemy Trait* models
to define key as String(255).

Closes-Bug: 1449752

Change-Id: I5ac2e9b811e3baa53e329732233cd0011a4d25b9

commit_message:
api: record severity change in alarm history

A useless change was done on the original alarm object when
we update the alarm. That have the side effect to hide the change
from the history.

This change fixes that

Change-Id: I9b3030dacf0da83bc0570ed4a6f9d460f178e2be
Closes-bug: #1452264

commit_message:
Fix 'vcenter_vlan_cindervmdk_cinder_ceph' test case

- mistake in test is following: it deploys cinder (LVM) and ceph nodes,
  but disables all block storage settings
- it is not possible to use both LVM and Ceph backends for Cinder
  simultaneously, so do not combine ceph-osd and cinder roles
- add multiple vCenter clusters to test cases 'vcenter_vlan_cindervmdk_cinder_ceph'
  and 'vcenter_vlan_cinder'
Change-Id: I72f7a3391a7934533dd21afb4e9936937b842f49
Closes-bug: #1450542

commit_message:
Fix api-site syncing

The check for api-site was wrong. Reworked the script so that it's
clearer what needs to be done for each project:
* Split up new function copy_glossary_xml
* Pass explicit parameter instead of global variables

Change-Id: I29cd7f3f7d2ce09e5a214633d292db793924eda0

commit_message:
Adds OCS Power and Management interfaces

Includes support for the Open CloudServer (OCS) chassis manager
power operations. The OCS design has been contributed by
Microsoft to the Open Compute project.

Implements blueprint msft-ocs-power-driver

Change-Id: Ic2c90ab5c8d79c55ae83dd485b3cf9281b600c23

commit_message:
Update galera_cluster stanza for HAproxy example

As Openstack support for multi-node writes to MySQL with Galera nodes
is not production ready yet (see
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-operators/2014-September/005166.html ),
update the HAproxy configuration example to use 2/3 nodes as a backup.

Closes-bug: #1419699

Change-Id: I3a6771a998f5962fac747ece47461e8c33228791
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobrelia@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
Fix Sahara installation for Ubuntu

Because Sahara does not support SQLite, sahara-common will fail to be
installed if /etc/sahara/sahara.conf does not contain valid database
connection and if the database does not actually exist.

The patch aims to
* create 'sahara' group (we don't use to do that, but here we don't have
  the choice)
* create /etc/sahara & /etc/sahara/sahara.conf with right permissions
* orchestration to have Sahara working in one Puppet run

Change-Id: I4c9e9206e3e60f3c85224ae120516badb331672e
Closes-bug: #1450659

commit_message:
Create Trove config before dbsync

Because packaging is trying to run dbsync while default config is
broken, as a woraround we manage Trove config *before* installing the
package so we can continue the installation with Puppet.

Also add a require to Package['trove-api'] on trove::db::sync class to
make sure trove-manage is installed before running the actual command.

This is a workaround and it could be reverted later when packaging issue
is triaged.

Change-Id: I82dc8b653bbbdc28bd165292649332310f252916
Partial-bug: #1451134

commit_message:
Engine: validate auth_encryption_key

When using a string with a length != 16, 24, or 32 as value for the
auth_encryption_key parameter in the /etc/heat/heat.conf file it is not
possible to create new stacks. Creating a new stack (and probably
anything else) will fail with the following exception:

ValueError: AES key must be either 16, 24, or 32 bytes long.

Change-Id: I4e35cf0f782f22861319d05a3f028e5784ad26d5
Closes-bug: #1415887

commit_message:
FWaaS: update packaging for Debian & Ubuntu

Ubuntu [1] and Debian [2] are now using neutron-fwaas.
Also cleaning unit-tests.

[1] http://packages.ubuntu.com/source/vivid/neutron-fwaas
[2] https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=783590

Closes-bug #1450589

Change-Id: Ia9c951941c2832b0c6e6b987ed64924b9c827195

commit_message:
Don't assert against all the lb-members

Assertion only needs to happen against the pool which
test_neutron_autoscaling.yaml creates, not against all the
lb-members that may exist.

Closes-Bug: #1446093

Change-Id: I2229a148460e68a7f9a1034edc91f2a6bc6cdf8b

commit_message:
Run dbsync as root and don't manage /etc/ironic & ironic.conf ownership

Ubuntu packaging is running dbsync command as root during ironic-common
postinstall script so when Puppet tries to run dbsync again, it fails
because it is run with ironic user.
So we need to run dbsync as root for now.
This is a temporary patch until it's changed in Packaging.

Also, don't manage user /etc/ironic & ironic.conf ownership and chmod to be packaging agnostic
(ubuntu & fedora use different permissions) and allow Puppet
idempotency.

Change-Id: Ia3571e4a212d9493604494bce5592da0831d9d7a
Partial-bug: #1450942

commit_message:
Update config generator to use oslo released libs

The adopted config generator script was using an older version
of gettextutils from oslo_incubator which is now available in
oslo.i18n and importutils from oslo.utils

Change-Id: I6814b64d69a14ba6374d5200894d57f9dea8de9e

commit_message:
Explicitly start and execute most transactions

Instead of having transactions that are not started
using the multi() block command ensure that we start at
the needed places to ensure that we correctly perform
these options in bulk (and handle the results of the
transaction running).

Change-Id: Idd5b91c466ccf11280d30619b1263e30d8d01708

commit_message:
Make _discover_extensions public

Heat uses `novaclient.shell.OpenStackComputeShell._discover_extensions`
function, which is private currently. It's better to change this method
to public for public use.

Change-Id: I15879d56db2ec88a9bef99b6af8924ebd4ad169b
Closes-bug: #1440779

Fix "app show" NotFound error message

an appropriate NotFound with the proper resource name.

commit_message:
Incorrect argument order passed to swap_volume

swap_volume method in _ComputeV4Proxy has incorrect
argument ordering, due to which attach volume migration
is failing with AttributeError
Modified the _ComputeV4Proxy detach_volume to have correct
argument ordering.

Change-Id: I899c053246f9eb4ac9b13a8434161a82193d1cef
Closes-Bug: #1451860
(cherry picked from commit 80832d9bb42da2b86853748874ad38dd30b9342d)

Hi Bruno,

You should use the same Change-Id yes, so that people can see the history of reviews.

The way you do it in git is:

1) Checkout to the branch where this change is.

2) Fix the problem

3) "git add" the files that you have touched/added (You can see the modified files by issuing "git status")

4) Ammend the changes to the previous commit, so it keep the same change-id). You can do it by issuing "git commit --amend"

5) Do a "git review" and it should create a new patch-set under this review :-)'}, {'account_id': 6773, 'date': '2015-05-05 11:32:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Specify environment variables needed for a standalone usage

Adds in the installation guide the info to setup the minimum
environment variables in order for ironic to work in
standalone mode.

Closes-Bug: #1451439

commit_message:
Adding unit test for taskflow service

- modified cue.taskflow.service to accept persistence and jobboard as an
  argument
- added a functional test to post a job to jobboard, launch a
  cue.taskflow.service instance, and have the job be consumed
- added unit tests to bring test coverage to 100%

Change-Id: I44bf335bc7b7ef7756e90184db34817b288ec5b6

Port to icehouse

This represents making build-docker-images --release build
with the icehouse tag and causes docker-compsoe to pull from
the icehouse tag.

commit_message:
Remove Zaqar for Icehouse

Zaqar was introduced in Juno, so remove it prior to branching
icehouse, then add it back in after branching icehouse.

Partially-implements: port-kilo

Change-Id: Icce95b4d404e6d8238206716e74f6826bc860860

commit_message:
Turn docs warnings into errors and fix issues

Set the pbr option 'warnerrors' to make build_sphinx turns warnings into
error. Fix all warnings.

`tox -edocs` will thus abort whenever someone introduce a new error.

Change-Id: Id6d09768a241866e1fdc1a1e2bf90336f5c5087d

why are we testing against a real /etc/ceilometer/ceilometer.conf again?'}, {'account_id': 11564, 'date': '2015-04-27 15:48:59.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

@gordon It's not intentional. I think the issue is that unless you explicitly state somewhere that you're not using a default location, then olso_cfg will go looking for a config file in that default location. I don't know what the knob is to twiddle that, thus the occasional fix in this vein.

I regularly run the tests on the same machine on which I regular run devstack so come across this fairly often.

I don't actually mind that the failures happen: I think it is a _bad_ idea for tests to have expectations about what will be in config and not set their expectations explicitly. My usual fix to this would be to instead of doing a set_override constructed the expected string from config, however the rest of the file had already set a precedent of using set_override."}, {'account_id': 6537, 'date': '2015-04-27 18:10:42.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

commit_message:
Override gnocchi_url configuration in test

Otherwise if there is an existing /etc/ceilometer/ceilometer.conf
then a test which matches on http://localhost:8041/ as the the base
of the gnocchi_url can fail.

Change-Id: I0a4e3a5e7dedc1f31cd53f032e126d12e29394e8

commit_message:
Make interval optional in pipeline

Make interval in pipeline yaml file optional. If interval is not
provided, a default value should be given.

Change-Id: I557e66902c272331bd1e2c72d03d495f0924d573
Closes-Bug: #1423957

commit_message:
sync oslo: service child process normal SIGTERM exit

service.py had some code where the child process would catch the
SIGTERM from the parent just so it could exit with 1 status rather
than with an indication that it exited due to SIGTERM. When
shutting down the parent doesn't care in what way the child ended,
only that they're all gone, so this code is unnecessary.

Also, for some reason this caused the child to never exit while
there was an open connection from a client. Probably something
with eventlet and signal handling.

Syncs commit: 702bc569987854b602ef189655c201c348de84cb

Change-Id: I3c5249f5e59bb396bcb50964907ea61ebb2a3c8a
Closes-Bug: #1446583
(cherry picked from commit f0f158af375efcc91e7c75859fceeec0111f424b)

commit_message:
IPv6 support for OpenSwan, Libreswan and Strongswan

VPNaaS is not working with IPv6 addresses.
This patch will address the below issues and make VPNaas
work with IPv6 addresses

1)ipsec doesn't need nat rule for ipv6. So not adding this for ipv6.
This issue is applicable for openSwan, libreswan and strongswan.

The below two issues are seen only on openswan and libreswan.
No changes are required to strongswan template files to support ipv6.
2)Add 'connaddrfamily=ipv6' to ipsec.conf for whack to parse all
addresses in the config as ipv6 addresses.

3)openswan fails to process ipv6 address from %defaultroute, so
explicitly pass the gateway address as leftnexthop address.

Change-Id: I74832be4476bd36cdcd4234b30d0daee24ef61ce
Closes-bug: #1435136
Closes-bug: #1436263
Closes-bug: #1436890

commit_message:
Fixed dashboard angular translation issue

We now have javascript files in openstack_dashboard as well. However,
the run_test script does not account for this and only run translation on
the horizon folder. This patch address this problem. Also removed the
invalid gettext('') since that causes the msgid to be blank.

Steps to test:
1. ./run_tests.sh --makemessages
2. ./run_tests.sh --pseudo de
3. ./run_tests.sh --compilemessages
4. set LAUNCH_INSTANCE_NG_ENABLED = True in local_settings.py
5. localhost:8001/settings/ and change to deutsch
6. localhost:port/project/instances/ and click on launch instance

Co-Authored-By: Doug Fish <drfish@us.ibm.com>
Change-Id: If1cd1937d40d359a4a4ecd75406f62e8f8802082

'ca_file': Specify a CA bundle file to use in verifying the vCenter

commit_message:
VMware: verify vCenter server certificate

Two configuration properties are being added:

'ca_file': Specify a CA bundle file to use in verifying the vCenter
server certificate

'insecure': If true, the vCenter server certificate is not verified.
If false, then the default CA truststore is used for verification.
This option is ignored if 'ca_file' is set.

Closes-Bug: #1276207

DocImpact

Change-Id: I8f408308cddbb40b19e8dc9fce6ff02745d963b8

[{'created': '2015-04-23 21:27:09.000000000', 'message': "Implement dangling mock detector for unittests

The Issue:

Dangling mock objects in global modules (mocked members of imported
modules that never get restored) have been causing various transient
failures in the unit test suite.

The main issues posed by dangling mock objects include:
- Such object references propagate across the entire test suite. Any
caller may be hit by a non-functional or worse crippled module member
because some other (potentially totally unrelated) test case failed to
restore it.
- Dangling mock references shared across different test modules may
lead to unexpected results/behavior in multi-threaded environments. One
example could be a test case failing because a mock got called multiple
times from unrelated modules.

Such issues are likely to exhibit transient random behavior depending
on the runtime environment making them difficult to debug.

This contribution is aiming to provide a simple transparent detection
layer that would help us prevent (most of) such issues.

Solution Strategy:

We extend the 'testtools.TestCase' class currently used as the base
class of Trove unit tests with functions that attempts to detect leaked
mock objects in imported modules. The new 'trove_testtools.TestCase'
implementation basically retrieves all loaded modules and scans their
members for mock objects before and after each test case.

An outline of the procedure follows:
1. Override the setUp() method and add a cleanup call (executed after
the tearDown()) to collect mock references before and after a test case.
2. Subtract the two sets after each test case and mark it as failed if
there are any new mock references left over.

Code Impact:

The existing test classes replace 'testtools.TestCase' base class with
'trove_testtools.TestCase'.

Documentation Impact:

Added a short document on recommended mocking strategies in unit tests
to the Trove Developer Documentation.

Known Limitations:

The current implementation currently descends only one level deep into
loaded modules meaning that while given the below import:

from some.package import module

it catches this: module.Class = Mock()
it does not detect this: module.Class.foo = Mock()

This limitation may be removed by adding a configurable recursion depth
to the mock search algorithm.

Recommended Mocking Patterns:

Mock Guide: https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.mock.html

- Mocking a class or object shared across multiple test cases.
  Use the patcher pattern in conjunction with the setUp() and tearDown()
  methods [ see section 26.4.3.5. of Mock Guide ].

def setUp(self):
    super(CouchbaseBackupTests, self).setUp()
    self.exe_timeout_patch = patch.object(utils, 'execute_with_timeout')

def test_case(self):
    # This line can be moved to the setUp() method if the mock object
    # is not needed.
    mock_object = self.exe_timeout_patch.start()

def tearDown(self):
    super(CouchbaseBackupTests, self).tearDown()
    self.exe_timeout_patch.stop()

Note also: patch.stopall()
Stop all active patches. Only stops patches started with start.

- Mocking a class or object for a single entire test case.
  Use the decorator pattern.

@patch.object(utils, 'execute_with_timeout')
@patch.object(os, 'popen')
def test_case(self, popen_mock, execute_with_timeout_mock):
    pass

@patch.multiple(utils, execute_with_timeout=DEFAULT,
		generate_random_password=MagicMock(return_value=1))
def test_case(self, generate_random_password, execute_with_timeout):
    pass

- Mocking a class or object for a smaller scope within one test case.
  Use the context manager pattern.

def test_case(self):
    # Some code using real implementation of 'generate_random_password'.
    with patch.object(utils, 'generate_random_password') as pwd_mock:
        # Using the mocked implementation of 'generate_random_password'.
    # Again code using the actual implementation of the method.

def test_case(self):
    with patch.multiple(utils, execute_with_timeout_mock=DEFAULT,
			generate_random_password=MagicMock(
				return_value=1)) as mocks:
     	password_mock = mocks['generate_random_password']
     	execute_mock = mocks['execute_with_timeout_mock']

Change-Id: Ia487fada249aa903410a1a3fb3f717d6e0d581d2
Conflicts:
	trove/tests/unittests/guestagent/test_backups.py

commit_message:
Implement dangling mock detector for unittests

The Issue:

Dangling mock objects in global modules (mocked members of imported
modules that never get restored) have been causing various transient
failures in the unit test suite.

The main issues posed by dangling mock objects include:
- Such object references propagate across the entire test suite. Any
caller may be hit by a non-functional or worse crippled module member
because some other (potentially totally unrelated) test case failed to
restore it.
- Dangling mock references shared across different test modules may
lead to unexpected results/behavior in multi-threaded environments. One
example could be a test case failing because a mock got called multiple
times from unrelated modules.

Such issues are likely to exhibit transient random behavior depending
on the runtime environment making them difficult to debug.

This contribution is aiming to provide a simple transparent detection
layer that would help us prevent (most of) such issues.

Solution Strategy:

We extend the 'testtools.TestCase' class currently used as the base
class of Trove unit tests with functions that attempts to detect leaked
mock objects in imported modules. The new 'trove_testtools.TestCase'
implementation basically retrieves all loaded modules and scans their
members for mock objects before and after each test case.

An outline of the procedure follows:
1. Override the setUp() method and add a cleanup call (executed after
the tearDown()) to collect mock references before and after a test case.
2. Subtract the two sets after each test case and mark it as failed if
there are any new mock references left over.

Code Impact:

The existing test classes replace 'testtools.TestCase' base class with
'trove_testtools.TestCase'.

Documentation Impact:

Added a short document on recommended mocking strategies in unit tests
to the Trove Developer Documentation.

Known Limitations:

The current implementation has a configurable recursion depth which is
the number of nested levels to examine when searching for mocks.
Higher setting will potentially uncover more dangling objects,
at the cost of increased scanning time.
We set it to 2 by default to get better coverage.
This setting will increase test runtime.

Recommended Mocking Patterns:

Mock Guide: https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.mock.html

- Mocking a class or object shared across multiple test cases.
  Use the patcher pattern in conjunction with the setUp() and tearDown()
  methods [ see section 26.4.3.5. of Mock Guide ].

def setUp(self):
    super(CouchbaseBackupTests, self).setUp()
    self.exe_timeout_patch = patch.object(utils, 'execute_with_timeout')

def test_case(self):
    # This line can be moved to the setUp() method if the mock object
    # is not needed.
    mock_object = self.exe_timeout_patch.start()

def tearDown(self):
    super(CouchbaseBackupTests, self).tearDown()
    self.exe_timeout_patch.stop()

Note also: patch.stopall()
Stop all active patches. Only stops patches started with start.

- Mocking a class or object for a single entire test case.
  Use the decorator pattern.

@patch.object(utils, 'execute_with_timeout')
@patch.object(os, 'popen')
def test_case(self, popen_mock, execute_with_timeout_mock):
    pass

@patch.multiple(utils, execute_with_timeout=DEFAULT,
                generate_random_password=MagicMock(return_value=1))

    pass

- Mocking a class or object for a smaller scope within one test case.
  Use the context manager pattern.

    with patch.object(utils, 'generate_random_password') as pwd_mock:
        # Using the mocked implementation of 'generate_random_password'.
    # Again code using the actual implementation of the method.

def test_case(self):
    with patch.multiple(utils, execute_with_timeout_mock=DEFAULT,
                        generate_random_password=MagicMock(
                                return_value=1)) as mocks:
        password_mock = mocks['generate_random_password']

[{'created': '2015-05-04 19:38:12.000000000', 'message': 'Adding /usr/local/etc/bandit/ to paths for Bandit config checking

When a user uses pip to install Bandit globally, the Bandit config
file is installed into /usr/local/etc/bandit, which is not one of
the paths which are checked during startup.  This leads to the
situation where a user runs "pip install bandit" and can't run
because they don't have a config file.  This commit fixes the
issue.

Change-Id: I5f971aa208dd2599f852b5253b4401990201cc8f

file is installed into /usr/local/etc/bandit, which is not one of
the paths which are checked during startup.  This leads to the
situation where a user runs "pip install bandit" and can't run
because they don't have a config file.  This commit fixes the
issue.

Change-Id: I5f971aa208dd2599f852b5253b4401990201cc8f
'}, {'created': '2015-05-06 14:45:04.000000000', 'message': "Changing config file search paths

This commit changes the location that the Bandit config file,
bandit.yaml, is stored and how it is packaged.  Previously, the
config file was listed as a data_file which is supposed to be
outside of the Bandit installed package.  This meant that
depending on the system it might be installed in different places
(/etc, or /usr/lcoal/etc, for example).  When Bandit was installed
in a virutal environment the installed location would change once
again.  Another disadvantage to this approach is that installing
Bandit might require sudo, and Bandit might not clean up its
config properly.

This commit changes the packaging so that bandit.yaml is always
installed in bandit/config/bandit.yaml.  If there is a bandit
config file in the current directory or the user's home directory,
these are still preferred.

commit_message:
Changing config file search paths

This commit changes the location that the Bandit config file,
bandit.yaml, is stored and how it is packaged.  Previously, the
config file was listed as a data_file which is supposed to be
outside of the Bandit installed package.  This meant that
depending on the system it might be installed in different places
(/etc, or /usr/lcoal/etc, for example).  When Bandit was installed
in a virutal environment the installed location would change once
again.  Another disadvantage to this approach is that installing
Bandit might require sudo, and Bandit might not clean up its
config properly.

This commit changes the packaging so that bandit.yaml is always
installed in bandit/config/bandit.yaml.  If there is a bandit
config file in the current directory or the user's home directory,
these are still preferred.

Change-Id: I5f971aa208dd2599f852b5253b4401990201cc8f

commit_message:
Added rsyslog logging support to object-server

Also change both proxy-server and object-server
.conf templates to test if log_udp_server and
log_udp_port are nil, instead of an empty string.
Testing for an empty string would have retruned
true if set to 'undef' - for futer parser compat.

Change-Id: Idac805f628dbec70a4adb6a1c021d85a743fdb72

commit_message:
Adding a check for the use of Assert

As noted in OSSN-0048, the use of assert to enforce runtime checks is
invalid. Assert should only be used for debug level checks.
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack/2015-April/012475.html

This change adds a new category of checks that can run on Assert AST
nodes.

Change-Id: I601d4d9a8d013c63e93dcbe7aa048e6ef87f2616

commit_message:
RemoteFS: Acquire lock when copy image to volume

Currently we are not acquiring any lock when copying image to
volume, because of this we can perform 'volume delete' operation
when it is 'downloading'.

This patch modifies the remotefs code to acquire lock on volume_id
when copy image to volume (method copy_image_to_volume).

Change-Id: I410a5a2efe66eb46694ac8de96d4cd3956d900af

commit_message:
Fix order of parameters for swap_volume (V4Proxy)

The compute manager's swap_volume() is being called with the
parameters in the wrong place.

Change-Id: I59fe42271ef2079fa3fbc92bd938c2bdd7fcc92e

commit_message:
libvirt: avoid call of listDefinedDomains when post live migration

The listDefinedDomains method would only return a list of
guests which have config files, but are *not* currently running. That
said after a live migration guests are running so this condition
will always pass.

Co-Authored-By Daniel Berrange <berange@redhat.com>

commit_message:
New test_patch helper script

This tool allows a single patch to be tested against the chef repo.
It will to do job of cloning the repo, merging in the patch(s),
setting up the test and running it, basic queries and tempest.

Also enhanced the Berksfile to allow for easy local development.

Usage: chef exec ruby test_patch.rb help test

Change-Id: I32ba57c29f2f5caee0391ea791ffe10fe06caceb

commit_message:
devtest_seed.sh add sbin in $PATH

The script expects `ip` command to be in the path. On Fedora, ip in /sbin,
which is not in the default $PATH of an user account.

This patch add /sbin and /usr/sbin in the current $PATH.

Change-Id: If6680670dd7a5cc92d6bc5c8581389faff725e4a

commit_message:
Add host counter to ansible inventory

Add host counter to the inventory. This is usedful to keep track of
known node offsets for log captures and overlay network setup.

Make use of the host counter to copy subnode logs to a known locations
to prove that this works as expected.

Change-Id: I2d2368d1546332ed1edc21eb0275df5bd8618825

Add dstat to subnode in multinode mode

Run and log dstat on the subnode in multinode to help make debugging
easier.

Change-Id: I944b26545642cb18fd2e1d5a375579d5a42cd92f

commit_message:
Link to config reference in our docs

The ironic configuration options for kilo are documented with the rest
of the OpenStack configs at
   http://docs.openstack.org/kilo/config-reference/content/.

This adds a 'Configuration Reference (Kilo)' entry to the index of our developer
documentation with a link to the config-reference URL. The install guide
also has a link to the config reference.

It also removes 'Bare Metal Service' from two entries at
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ironic/, since it seems redundant.
(Everything there is about Bare Metal Service!)

Change-Id: Idf649641b2108ac6075e7b67c547551bccd9d5f7

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-05-05 02:45:53.000000000', 'message': "Don't create empty quota set requests

The way that getattr is called with the None default you will always
create a compute_kwargs dictionary with key: None values. This means
that we will always send these empty requests to the servers.

Change so that only actually changed values end up in the quota set
requests and get sent.

Change-Id: I33bc3f4e1a8013ec672e995648d27513064baf26
Closes-Bug: #1451640
"}]
commit_message:
Don't create empty quota set requests

The way that getattr is called with the None default you will always
create a compute_kwargs dictionary with key: None values. This means
that we will always send these empty requests to the servers.

Change so that only actually changed values end up in the quota set
requests and get sent.

Change-Id: I33bc3f4e1a8013ec672e995648d27513064baf26
Closes-Bug: #1451640

commit_message:
Add docs for service provider CRUD

This patch adds service providers to command-objects, and makes
a few changes to the help text, to align it more with the
already established identity provider resource.

Change-Id: Ibf3d2bc04bf5588d1fc9c37b8ca28c007496c021

commit_message:
Added collection error catching

Errors while collecting service data are now handled properly and logged
and don't make CloudKitty crash anymore.

Change-Id: Ia1efb06d7ba38973af8d210fc99b7aed129c5fc6

commit_message:
Updated oslo_middleware to 1.2.0

This version of oslo_middleware includes new CORS support,
permitting API's to selectively break the browser's single-origin
policy. Its usage is optional.

Relevant Specification: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/179866/

commit_message:
Remove instance_uuid as part of tear_down

Ironic uses the node's instance_uuid field to associate a node with
an instance. But, when used as a standalone service Ironic does not remove
the instance association after unprovisioned the node, leaving it
associated with something that doesn't exist anymore (Node's back to
"available" provision_state, instance_info is empty, disks are cleanered
etc...).

Currently only the Nova Ironic driver is removing the instance association
as part of their destroy() method, I think Ironic should do it instead,
since we also clean up other fields like the Node's instance_info.

Also, this patch doesn't break the Nova driver it won't fail when trying
to remove the instance_uuid. In fact we should leave it there for this
cycle for backwards compatibility and remove it from there in the M cycle.

Change-Id: Ibb54e3d18e3f63d3988ac2e7e38bb18623caa10f

commit_message:
Allow to re-define release/version parameters for rpmbuild

1) We can re-define release and version parameters while building
   package(s) (for rpmbuild):
     * --define "release $RELEASE"
     * --define "version $VERSION"

2) fuel-package-updates.spec has been moved to fuel-web project

Change-Id: I3378c9e92151f94c3496869a333a457705e4a9d3
Related-blueprint:  package-fuel-components

commit_message:
rabbit/qpid: simplify the consumer loop

The consumer loop is over engineered, it returns unused return,
iterconsume creates an iterator directly consumed by 'consume' without
special handling, and in some case kombu error callback are called when
the iterator is stopped and log useless error.

And in reality the consumer is always called when limit=1.

This change simplifies that, by removing the loop and removes all
returns stuffs.

Closes bug: #1450336

Change-Id: Ia2cb52c8577b29e74d4d2b0ed0b535102f2d55c7

[{'created': '2014-12-02 03:50:53.000000000', 'message': "Construct v3 auth_url when keystoneclient discover doesn't support it

So far, keystoneclient discover still doesn't support keystone v3
auth_url. In this case, v2 auth_url will be directly used by
os-collect-config to get authentication and thus cause 404 error.
This patch try to fix this issue by constructing a correct v3 auth_url
when we can't get it from keystoneclient discover.

Change-Id: I45b4c016bd91afc39d39620920951043bb71df05
Closes-Bug: #1398254

commit_message:
Use non-versioned auth_url for keystone

keystoneclient discover can't get v3 auth_url using v2 auth_url. It
accepts an url without version number. This patch fixes this issue.

Change-Id: I45b4c016bd91afc39d39620920951043bb71df05
Closes-Bug: #1398254

commit_message:
Pass through arbitrary devstack config options

Use the var DEVSTACK_LOCAL_CONFIG in job templates
to pass through arbitrary devstack config options.

This change updates some jobs templates to use it
instead of using custom devstack-gate options.

Change-Id: I01dc762f0ba1bc52bdeb5c434039bd5ab30cce1e

When running MySQL for storage backend, we need to make sure
python-mysqldb is installed *before* the db_sync command, otherwise it
will fail:
"ImportError: No module named MySQLdb".

This patch ensure the ordering to ensure puppetlabs-mysql installed the
package before puppet-ceilometer tries to synchronize the MySQLdatabase.

Change-Id: Iae7c8f24fda32357a61ffa3b8597dd3413c303cb
'}]
commit_message:
Ensure python-mysqldb is installed  before MySQL db_sync

When running MySQL for storage backend, we need to make sure
python-mysqldb is installed *before* the db_sync command, otherwise it
will fail:
"ImportError: No module named MySQLdb".

This patch ensure the ordering to ensure puppetlabs-mysql installed the
package before puppet-ceilometer tries to synchronize the MySQLdatabase.

Change-Id: Iae7c8f24fda32357a61ffa3b8597dd3413c303cb

commit_message:
Clean build dir before building plugin package

If there are some artifacts left in build dir, for example old
RPMs may cause different side effects like having two version of
packages of the same plugin in the end of the build.

Change-Id: I427065cad0c1e610b637d312e91c60fd521ea14e
Closes-Bug: #1451751

commit_message:
WIP - wsgi/apache: refactore to use openstacklib

Refactorize some code to use openstacklib::wsgi::apache function to
configure Keystone as a WSGI process with Apache2.

Still need to fix some cases. Also, I'm not sure this is really useful
for keystone.

Change-Id: I5c082c7e374d53226e312d83a97afb318b481cc7

relocation, HA and DVR.

commit_message:
Optionally pass regex to skip to tempest-dsvm-full-plugin jobs

Allow passing of a regex to the template, set template to empty so that
it's not used currently.

This allows to reuse the job with a regex for tempest without
duplicating it. This should make the change for
I3487db550ba0966e60779b955b6796a03d2690a5 much easier.

Change-Id: I83dacde928137778d75da75ee4baf37cf8a86328

commit_message:
Rename tempest-dsvm-full-{plugin}

To avoid name collisions - which might be difficult to debug - rename
tempest-dsvm-full-{plugin} to tempest-dsvm-full-plugin-{plugin}.
This way it's clear that for example tempest-dsvm-full-ceph, is not
using the plugin template.

Change-Id: I81ad28c79ad980502fa34c8083fed7ad22da03b3

Revert "Set mtu for internal networks according to segmentation type"

This reverts commit 0d73bfe19c405b186ae2e86ead351ca51db0b22a.
The path 'vendor_specific' is wrong and should not be used for
the management interface evaluation.

Related-bug: #1411732

Change-Id: I577f60363f5dd443755c6d0ace514b08ebc77b76

commit_message:
Fix ubuntu grub-pc install failure

When creating an ubuntu image with localboot, the postinst script
of grub-pc will try to find root device and install grub which will
definitely fail in such a chroot environment.

Closes-Bug: #1437548
Change-Id: Ia29387f33c33e760c2711c687a43025b2013bd84

commit_message:
Add Python SDK to PROJECTS for SDK gate

The gate is saying:

    bash: /opt/stack/new/python-openstacksdk/post_test_hook.sh: No such file or directory

I assume the problem is the SDK project was not checked out.

Change-Id: I9b2c1d0b10c3672d5deb1b16b16b01054e502804

Since DIB creates a chroot but doesn't actually chroot in an
extra-data script, look for /etc/redhat-release relative to the
temporary chroot base path. Also given that the centos element
leaves DIB_RELEASE exported as am empty string in the calling

Change-Id: I0a51f88ff5ea71b6aa6e6406b656cefb0e135e88
"}]
commit_message:
Do a better job of identifying CentOS 6

Since DIB creates a chroot but doesn't actually chroot in an
extra-data script, look for /etc/redhat-release relative to the
temporary chroot base path. Also given that the centos element
leaves DIB_RELEASE exported as am empty string in the calling
environment rather than unset, place it first in the conditional
list.

Change-Id: I0a51f88ff5ea71b6aa6e6406b656cefb0e135e88

[{'created': '2015-05-04 03:22:58.000000000', 'message': 'Look for yum instead of rpm when caching devstack

On CentOS 6.x the rpm executable is in /bin instead of /usr/bin, but
cache_devstack.py ends up running yum if it wants to download RPM
packages anyway. Look for yum instead of rpm as an indication of
which packages to install.

Change-Id: Iad79c0fcf66d2bd457195f007009c76f6e6aa2d2
'}]
commit_message:
Look for yum instead of rpm when caching devstack

On CentOS 6.x the rpm executable is in /bin instead of /usr/bin, but
cache_devstack.py ends up running yum if it wants to download RPM
packages anyway. Look for yum instead of rpm as an indication of
which packages to install.

Change-Id: Iad79c0fcf66d2bd457195f007009c76f6e6aa2d2

commit_message:
[Clients] Add classmethod osclients.Clients.register

Classmethod osclients.Clients.register allows to add new
OpenStack clients to Rally at runtime, so these clients will
be available from osclients.Clients and cached.

Change-Id: I644aa2b742a8433f90068ae95328f5d0ef6b27dc

commit_message:
Print name of invalid option in error message

When a configuration value is invalid, currently it just prints the
value, without the name of the option that is invalid. This change
outputs the name of the option and the invalid value.

Change-Id: I32b1d819ac2e0d2c9d9e38b04b6c260278f54126

commit_message:
Check for mount before creating swap

The existing umount appears to be just for safety, as it does not
actually unmount anything.  It fails with errexit, but rather than
ignore this, it seems better to check if there is a mount and bail
out.

If somehow the ephemeral storage was mounted, it implies somebody set
it up somewhere else and wouldn't be expecting this to go ahead and
repartition it on them.

Change-Id: Id7d345130b751973d997940d7b62a4c253d265ed

[{'created': '2015-04-30 02:34:52.000000000', 'message': 'Make sysctl vm dump errexit safe

Ubuntu 12.02 era procps doesn't understand 0200 write-only "trigger"
nodes in /proc (particularly the vm.compact node to start memory
compaction) and returns an invalid error.  Ignore this to make it
errexit safe.  Later versions of procps skip over such nodes.

Change-Id: I29385156a258bc604cf82f54ff98d81a22d38e5b
'}]
commit_message:
Make sysctl vm dump errexit safe

Ubuntu 12.02 era procps doesn't understand 0200 write-only "trigger"
nodes in /proc (particularly the vm.compact node to start memory
compaction) and returns an invalid error.  Ignore this to make it
errexit safe.  Later versions of procps skip over such nodes.

Change-Id: I29385156a258bc604cf82f54ff98d81a22d38e5b

commit_message:
Remove pip cache move

This bit is, I believe, no longer relevant.  As far as I can tell it
was introduced in Iee0a946afa80929e99c08e5a6b0504c1d8dd0093 with the
comment "actually move the pip cache into the place devstack expects".
These days we have pip setup to use the pypi.openstack.org repos.

Since the command fails, this breaks running the script with errexit.

Change-Id: If444cf8fd495f495fc96e8b01cf11f3b311f46ca

commit_message:
Remove heat from default configuration

There is now a heat specific tempest job. So Heat is no longer needed in
the default configuration of the integrated gate.

Change-Id: I70a20f36b333d7626751b099020f8f91c02cd147
Depends-On: I03fb778035926b6739394b64b370a245d31346c1

commit_message:
Archive glusterfs logs and config

We should archive the glusterfs logs and config files when we run
the check-tempest-dsvm-full-glusterfs-nv job to help in debugging
failures.

Change-Id: I6de5b6f18a464a6e93df426185466cbc2791698b

commit_message:
libvirt: introduce new method to guest tablet device

Introduces a new method to help returning the
usb tablet device configuration of the domain xml.

Related-To: blueprint virt-configure-usb-tablet-from-image

Change-Id: Idffa7db835ecf4228a54b1bf5bb0d3cbd93b6e7a

'}, {'created': '2015-04-15 04:25:20.000000000', 'message': "Refactor the bandwidth_usage object's remotable method

1. The object.base.serialize_args decorator can only convert datetime to
timestamp string if the parameter is passed in kwargs. Refactor the
bandwidth_usage object's remotable method to make sure datetime is
always converted to timestamp string.

2. Convert timestamp string in bandwidth_usage object to timezone aware
datetime for the DB API call.

3. In sqlalchemy DB API, make sure datetime is UTC native.

Change-Id: Icbf9ff73b867a5cc3bb9f5eb6a13ad954d7c44f6
Closes-Bug: #1442795

commit_message:
Convert bandwidth_usage related timestamp to UTC native datetime

In sqlalchemy DB API, convert timestamp string related to
bandwidth_usage operations into UTC native datetime.

Closes-Bug: #1442795
Change-Id: Icbf9ff73b867a5cc3bb9f5eb6a13ad954d7c44f6

commit_message:
console: clean tokens do not happen for all kind of consoles

The current condition to verify whether or not consoles are
enable and so flush tokens when destroying instance is not
kept sync with every kind of consoles that can be enable.

This commit create one entry point to clean tokens + update the
missing serial console config.

Already covered by tests.

Closes-Bug: #1451801
Change-Id: Ie7cb03a9431549df75d7fbc82cf19e3f8f410a0f

commit_message:
Remove orphaned tables - iscsi_targets, volumes

The `iscsi_targets` and `volumes` table was used with nova-volumes,
which is deprecated and removed, but the related tables are still created.

DocImpact

Closes-Bug: #1426867
Change-Id: I7d70bee6fa1b43590222ff637e1328e2953c9916

commit_message:
Use a serialization/deserialization specific exception

Instead of raising the top level tooz error on loads/dumps
failures, instead raise a specific one that is only used
when serialization/deserialization has some sort of issue.

This also changes the exception raised in the memcache driver
to also use this new exception type (when a unknown serialization
format is encountered).

Change-Id: Ic4302b1bf3dba45b70af85a081bebbe0512c6830

commit_message:
Fix management IPs usage

Fixed improper usage of management IPs.
Almost all cluster configuration relies on internal IPs

Closes-Bug: #1449506
Closes-Bug: #1439461

commit_message:
Describes Ceilometer support for vCenter in 6.1

In 6.1 release, Ceilometer agent is installed on the same node
as Controller and Compute.
This provides metrics collection for the instances.

The issue will be covered in the corresponding
section of User Guide.

Change-Id: I083e149a598b8fb6a5422ffb5f2c3f2fd9b52072
Implements: blueprint ceilometer-support-for-vcenter

commit_message:
Add a gitreview default target for gerrit for kilo

If people were to submit changes to the kilo branch, they would
be applied to master.  This patch makes the default gerrit target
stable/kilo.

Change-Id: I3594070526382ed0a893f16ca8c63cf81d7b2ba7

commit_message:
added chef-rake-jobs for openstack-chef-repo

chef-rake-jobs should also be run for the master and all following
releases of the openstack-chef-repo and was forgotten in the last patch
for all the other cookbook-openstack-{name} repos

commit_message:
Implement tosca.capabilities.Container

1. Move num_cpus,disk_size,mem_size of tosca.node.Compute to
tosca.capabilities.Container.
2. Change all template files involves these properties.
3. Fix some unittests which become failed because of properties change.

Co-Authored-By: Sahdev Zala <spzala@us.ibm.com>

Blueprint tosca-container-capabilities

Change-Id: I107ee3906765fb4e2b1497a78433b1095eb7b792

commit_message:
Fix setting up of ODL package variables

When we changed [1], we inadvertently broke some logic that needed
the modified variables to remain changed after download of ODL [2].

Patch 2: install xpath, if needed
Patch 3: use is_opendaylight_enabled instead of looking at enabled services
Patch 4: more moving around, to make changes smaller
Patch 5: avoid multiple wgets for ${NEXUSPATH}/${BUNDLEVERSION}/maven-metadata.xml
Patch 6: move exported common variables into a function: configure_odl_pkg_vars
Patch 7: implement code review feedback

[1]: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/179129/
[2]: https://jenkins.opendaylight.org/releng/view/ovsdb/job/ovsdb-openstack-gerrit/1708/artifact/logs/devstacklog.txt

Change-Id: Icb1dc717d286e62e7fee5efef8fb47ddb3c6c798

commit_message:
Add heat-api-cfn

Add Heat-api-cfn for wait conditions

Magnum needs wait conditions in order to operate properly.  heat-api-cfn
is where wait conditions connect.

Change-Id: I56742dd96e4607dc0042d0cef4e18c922f9ed736
Implements: blueprint container-heat-api-cfn

commit_message:
Make neutron-server upgrade the database to head

Rather then upgrading to a specific version of OpenStack, just
upgrade to Head.  This works for both juno and kilo.

Change-Id: I6305218eabd7de0878e24c8fdae968ac6d612175
Partially-implements: blueprint port-kilo

Use oslo_log lib

Module 'log' from oslo-incubator was removed after release of oslo_log library.

Change-Id: I4261083dae076cea66c42ad16eb82a5faaeb1a65

commit_message:
Include graphviz in install prerequisites

Graphviz is needed for generating the state machine diagram
(eg, via 'tox -egenstates'). It is added to the list of packages
to install.

The instructions for installing on openSUSE and SLE are a bit
more involved, so I've added a URL that describes how to do that.

Change-Id: I16380bc88fcecc6911f21b4554b04a9d72b2d66b

Add gate hooks to be able to control the gate workflow easily. This adds
a hook that runs before the test and one that runs after the test.

commit_message:
Rotate docker container logs

With the current rotation policy, container stdout/stderr
will be rotated as needed if the size exceeds 10MB. Should
not impact properly running docker containers for the output
of docker logs CONTAINER

Change-Id: Id09f562b07c4a55d0d11678bede94cc15aecd937
Closes-Bug: #1450305

commit_message:
Update name of Ubuntu vagrant box

This fixes an error in Vagrant, where an error occurs when trying
to run "vagrant up":

	The box you're adding has a name different from the name you
	requested. For boxes with metadata, you cannot override the name.
	If you're adding a box using `vagrant box add`, don't specify
	the `--name` parameter. If the box is being added via a Vagrantfile,
	change the `config.vm.box` value to match the name below.

	Requested name: ubuntu1404
	Actual name: ubuntu/trusty64

Change-Id: If0a5eb34d3309baa085e8cfd69167ab07867be9f

commit_message:
Adds publish-to-pypi to networking-hyperv

Previously, pypi-jobs was added to jenkins/jobs/projects.yaml
but publish-to-pypi was not added to zuul/layout.yaml.

This commit corrects the issue.

Commit for pypi-jobs: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/178993/

Change-Id: I93ecc35567f1c78a090bf57909fb4168146dc5b5

commit_message:
Adds pypi-jobs to compute-hyperv

Pushing a version through gerrit should also publish version
to pypi.

Pypi project: https://pypi.python.org/pypi?name=compute-hyperv
openstackci is added as admin user.

commit_message:
Adds refs/heads/stable/* to compute-hyperv

Commit necessary in order to create new branches in
compute-hyperv. This will allow the creation of the
stable/kilo branch.

Change-Id: Ifd6bbcdcbeb13f1fd158b188eb73e356b3197d94

commit_message:
[Spec] Reorder plugins

Rally has billions of plugins and it becomes really hard for newbies
to understand how Rally code is organized and how it works.

So let's split framework and plugins

Example https://review.openstack.org/#/c/176092/

Change-Id: I6980c0dcbeeabf79e774c69cd27e5e4efca0fc50

commit_message:
Deprecate config-based Quota Driver

This patch displays a deprecation warning everytime the quota
driver neutron.quota.ConfDriver is loaded.
The driver will be removed in the "M" cycle.

Change-Id: Ifb799755bce50bb089f8df020286fd2e95c80a68
Closes-Bug: #1430523

commit_message:
Disable invalid sort key in list command

The 'node_uuid' is an invalid sort key in port list command, as
well as 'chassis_uuid' in node list command.
Remove them from sort keys in corresponding list commands.

Change-Id: I10caf5d99d9c8cc7b03dedc9b5cf0546351c6657
Closes-Bug: #1443003

New change set just pushed with a fix for the docstring
and more elaboration in the commit message on why we
are re-working these unit tests.

We got into this predicament because submethods of do_setup were not mocked out and threw the same exception as that which was expected.  In consequence, our unit tests failed to detect the logic error in do_setup.

The callcount zero assertions here distinguish between the case where we get the expected exception from the mount call attempt and the case where set_nas_security_options triggers that exception. If this were a little utility function, we could ignore it, but it's a big external method with OS interactions, significant side effects, and its own callouts to more methods with the same characteristics. We shouldn't be looking into these to see if they could throw the expected exceptions (OSError? NFSException?) or not, nor should we be counting in our unit tests that its implementation does not change.  mocking it out and asserting that we didn't invoke it provides assurance that the exceptions we see came from the part of do_setup that is under test.

With respect to the quantity of tests, each test represents a distinct code path in do_setup and it seemed most efficient to address the whole set of do_setup tests in one commit even though their scope is greater than the single part of do_setup where we changed code."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-21 20:40:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Verified-1

[{'created': '2015-04-20 21:08:38.000000000', 'message': 'Fix range check for NFS used ratio

The nfs_used_ratio configuration parameter is supposed to be
greater than zero and less than or equal to one.  However,
current configuration checks actually allow values greater
than one because of a logic error.  Unit tests fail to detect
this issue because they find the exception that they expect
to find, but it is actually being thrown for another reason.

This commit fixes the logic error in the nfs driver code and
reworks the NFS do_setup unit tests so that they do proper mocks
and avoid triggering extraneous, misleading exceptions.  The
unit tests for do_setup are moved to their own test class,
where mock is used rather than mox.  Over time it is likely
that new tests will be implemented, or old tests reworked,
with mock instead of mox.  These can go in the new test class,
which can be renamed if that is appropriate.

Change-Id: I19ab396057fb6f60ad8e7d10944384db7e95ece6
Fixes-bug: 1445786

The nfs_used_ratio configuration parameter is supposed to be
greater than zero and less than or equal to one.  However,
current configuration checks actually allow values greater
than one because of a logic error.  Unit tests fail to detect
this issue because they find the exception that they expect
to find, but it is actually being thrown for another reason.

This commit fixes the logic error in the nfs driver code.

It also reworks all the unit tests for the do_setup method since
they suffer from the same issue that led to failure to detect
this error in the first place - they fail to do proper mocks of

commit_message:
Fix range check for NFS used ratio

The nfs_used_ratio configuration parameter is supposed to be
greater than zero and less than or equal to one.  However,
current configuration checks actually allow values greater
than one because of a logic error.  Unit tests fail to detect
this issue because they find the exception that they expect
to find, but it is actually being thrown for another reason.

This commit fixes the logic error in the nfs driver code.

It also reworks all the unit tests for the do_setup method since
they suffer from the same issue that led to failure to detect
this error in the first place - they fail to do proper mocks of
submethods, and when these run the expected exception gets triggered
for the wrong reason.  We have moved these tests into their own test
class, where mock is used rather than mox.  Over time it is likely
that new tests will be implemented, or old tests reworked, with mock
instead of mox.  These can go in the new test class, which can be
renamed if that is appropriate.

Change-Id: I19ab396057fb6f60ad8e7d10944384db7e95ece6
Fixes-bug: 1445786

commit_message:
Fix account replication during pre-storage-policy upgrade

Old account schemas don't send the storage_policy_index key for container rows
during replication, and if the recieving end is already running an upgraded
server it is surprised with a KeyError.  Normally this would work itself out
if the old schema recieved any updates from container layer, or a new
container is created, or requires a row sync from another account database -
but if the account databases have rows out of sync and there's no activity in
the account otherwise, there's nothing to force the old schemas to be
upgraded.

Rather than force the old schema that already has a complete set of container
rows to migrate even in the absense of activity we can just fill in default
legacy value for the storage policy index and allow the accounts to get back
in sync and migrate the next time a container update occurs.

FWIW, I never able to get a cluster upgrade to get stuck in this state without
some sort of account failure that forced them to get their rows out of sync
(in my cause I just unlinked a pending and then made sure to force all my
account datbases to commit pending files before upgrading - leading to an
upgraded cluster that absolutly needed account-replication to solve a row
mismatch for inactive accounts with old schemas)

Closes-Bug #1424108

Change-Id: Iaf4ef834eb24f0e11a52cc22b93a864574fabf83

commit_message:
Extend Zaqar's gate jobs

This patch extends zaqar's jobs so that they use the various hooks
correctly and allow for other scripts to be maintained by the zaqar team
itself.

Summary:
- Add support for external gate_hook
- Add support for external post_gate_hook

Change-Id: Ia72e6b2bf66005728bacc4ed850a9aa16c6519a2

commit_message:
Make zaqarclient functional gate non-voting

This is a temporary patch while we fix the gate. We need to get pools
enabled in Zaqar's devstack lib to make this gate work again. Until we
do that, we should not block client's patches.

Change-Id: Ia5ce4817bdbf4110f4786982299cbbd5600ae45e

commit_message:
Expose redis client class constants

These constants are quite useful to have show up in
the generated docs and do no harm if they are made public
since they are expected to be constant so make them public
and add docstrings to them so they appear in the docs.

Change-Id: Ia3d179a58cca584abd4bdfc069a96a6d9533c36a

commit_message:
Use an auth plugin instead of manual auth

Heat used to construct it's own authentication request so that it could
specify ?nocatalog for fetching a token without a service catalog. This
can be done using the keystoneclient plugins rather than constructing
this auth request.

Change-Id: I3216921b5a9f0f21f8c3283fd8d7e81916718b96

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-05-06 07:04:38.000000000', 'message': "Execute subtasks in FakeVerificationThread

The verification task could contain a various subtasks (e.g. check_dhcp),
but FakeVerificationThread doesn't even try to execute them. As result,
we have hanged tasks (status = 'running') in the database. In order to
avoid this issue, we have to pass execution to subtasks before executing
the verification task, just like Astute behaves.

Closes-Bug: #1448934

Change-Id: I4ce15ad482f423e3c9be646314b6b4610f732f51
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>
"}]
commit_message:
Execute subtasks in FakeVerificationThread

The verification task could contain a various subtasks (e.g. check_dhcp),
but FakeVerificationThread doesn't even try to execute them. As result,
we have hanged tasks (status = 'running') in the database. In order to
avoid this issue, we have to pass execution to subtasks before executing
the verification task, just like Astute behaves.

Closes-Bug: #1448934

Change-Id: I4ce15ad482f423e3c9be646314b6b4610f732f51
Signed-off-by: Igor Kalnitsky <igor@kalnitsky.org>

commit_message:
Catch additional type conversion errors

When converting strings to integers in quota we catch ValueError which
will handle an input which is not a valid number, eg 'abc'. Extend this
to covert TypeErrors which will handle things like a None value being
passed.

Partial-Bug: #1451637
Change-Id: I7e3e694d539113beeb99001aeb80012ac4c1124d

commit_message:
Expose memcache coord. class constants

These constants are quite useful to have show up in
the generated docs and do no harm if they are made public
since they are expected to be constant so make them public
and add docstrings to them so they appear in the docs.

Change-Id: Ife77f7dd32d26428a58605ca4cc2d1e6e2abe88d

commit_message:
Fix dsvm gate failure

Tempest module 'auth' was moved into tempest-lib repo, this change
caused import error, that was fixed in this commit.

commit_message:
Use auth plugin provided getter methods

The auth plugins provide a get_user_id and get_project_id function that
allows plugins that don't use an AccessInfo object to return this
information. We should use those instead of get_access.

Change-Id: I565139f5b8a3c749a928ce0fcc3f1ab6eda81d83

commit_message:
Rename 'tags' to be 'metadata'

According to guidelines from API workgroup, we should not call the
'tags' field 'tags'. They are actually 'metadata', i.e. dictionaries
that can contain key-value pairs. 'Tags', on the other hand, is used to
refer to a list of strings. This patch fixes the DB, service, test cases
and docs to make Senlin conformant to this guideline.

Change-Id: I9692947cd02cce7f575c0bed56aa2c37e23170e4

commit_message:
Forbid deleting a policy in use

This patch added a check before policy deleting to prevent user
from deleting a policy that is still attached to cluster(s).

Change-Id: I695fa9d6501b4f7afba6ca27ed546612193843ac

commit_message:
Remove "OPTIONAL:" from optional argument help text (v2)

All arguments starting with '--' are optional and listed
under the 'Optional arguments:' header by argparse.  Remove
the extra note shown for each argument.

This mirrors the previous change which cleaned this up for v1:
811af8f Remove "OPTIONAL:" from optional argument help text

Change-Id: Ie8e9544c1544ff5403f1c29e83d528d896957899

commit_message:
Install heat-contrib-extraroute wheel

Currently, we git clone heat source onto heat_engine containers and
install selected plugins via a 'python setup.py install'.  This change
removes the tasks that do that and simply adds heat-contrib-extraroute
to heat_pip_packages so it gets installed on all heat-related
containers.  This is actually only required on the heat_engine
containers but the package is tiny and should not cause any issues
being present on the heat_api containers.

Change-Id: I3aa81f8a8697505b9aa6e25a453d88f07714998c

So for clarity: you'll need to keep this no lower than the version in the root setup.cfg. Because pbr uses git history,  its simply not possible to issue version numbers for these subdirectories that are lower than the version numbers for the git history. It is possible to make them lower than the version for the whole tree if you use preversioning for the root setup.cfg and postversioning for the subdirectories.

If having separate version numbers is actually a key use case, I think you're going to need to use git submodules (or just regular git trees) for these things.

I don't understand why pip wouldn't be able to install the sdisted contents without a version line, since that would merely use the git history directly without the artifical bump of preversioning. http://docs.openstack.org/developer/pbr/#version

commit_message:
Update version in each contrib plugin's setup.cfg

Currently, contrib plugins are not build-able due to changes in pbr
version 0.11.0.  Each plugin is configured with a version of 0.1
which is < the most recent tag (2015.1.0.0rc2).  This commit bumps
the version of each plugin to the next heat version (2015.2) as
suggested in bug/1450733.

Note that the versioning of 0.1 and up was originally suggested so
that plugins could be properly installed with pip while keeping a
separation between heat itself and the unsupported plugins.  However,
removing the the version altogether results in plugins being built
with a version of the latest tag (2015.1.0.0rc2).  Using that tag
version does not seem to have any real benefit and in fact will
probably only cause confusion.

Change-Id: I27b385f7e600be4e5805ebce86b9a193acedcdce
Closes-Bug: #1450733

commit_message:
Replace all occurrences of $ with $$ in vCenter input values

- OpenStack services may reference to previously defined variable in
  configuration files using $ (dollar sign), e.g. 'metadata_host =
  $my_ip'.  Interpolation can be avoided by using $$.  Passwords often
  contain metachars and $ is one of them.  We must replace all $
  occurrences with $$, otherwise service will fail to start because it
  cannot interpolate non-existing variable.
- add static method escape_dollar() to VMwareDeploymentSerializerMixin
  class that implements conversion
- also handle username and regular expression that is used for datastore
  search
- provide input values with '$' in test fixture vmware_attributes.json
- modify integration test

Change-Id: I0d7d9f2d7f0ccaa3310c865a7f467c377c067442
Closes-bug: #1436083

[{'created': '2015-04-28 07:41:04.000000000', 'message': 'Add "bifrost" to Ironic project

Bifrost is a set of ansible playbooks and roles that demonstrate how to
configure and use Ironic to provision hardware, without requiring any
other OpenStack services.

This is useful as a CI tool and as a minimal deployment tool for small

commit_message:
Add "bifrost" to Ironic project

Bifrost is a set of ansible playbooks and roles that demonstrate how to
configure and use Ironic to provision hardware, without requiring any
other OpenStack services.

This is useful as a CI tool and as a minimal deployment tool for small
environments where shared resource management is not needed.

Change-Id: I2552803a1da44312a0e8879629036a23d89e2e2a

commit_message:
Add CLI read-only functional tests

First pass at functional tests in cinderclient.  This patch
just takes some of the basic CLI tests from tempest and moves
them into the cinderclient functional tests.

These are read-only tests, and just do simple field checks
on the tables generated by the basic list commands.

Note: to run use "tox -efunctional", this requires that you
have a full cinderclient env and credentials are set. You may
be either running this locally (say in a devstack env) or
you may have a remote cloud handy that you can just source the
credentials for and run it that way.

Change-Id: I2f09a63be265d6a74cb103d80579068b9ab66bf4

subject: Add sync mechanism between neutron DB and OVN-NB DB
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 105, 'name': 'Kyle Mestery', 'email': 'mestery@mestery.com', 'username': 'mestery'}, {'_account_id': 1561, 'name': 'Russell Bryant', 'email': 'rbryant@redhat.com', 'username': 'russellb'}, {'_account_id': 1653, 'name': 'garyk', 'email': 'gkotton@vmware.com', 'username': 'garyk'}, {'_account_id': 4395, 'name': 'Aaron Rosen', 'email': 'aaronorosen@gmail.com', 'username': 'arosen'}, {'_account_id': 5756, 'name': 'Terry Wilson', 'email': 'twilson@redhat.com', 'username': 'otherwiseguy'}, {'_account_id': 11343, 'name': 'Gal Sagie', 'email': 'gal.sagie@gmail.com', 'username': 'GalSagie'}, {'_account_id': 13070, 'name': 'Eran Gampel', 'email': 'eran@gampel.net', 'username': 'Gampel'}]
messages:
[{'account_id': 11343, 'date': '2015-04-16 15:14:55.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2015-04-16 15:33:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I just thought of a design issue.  Consider the case of doing an OpenStack upgrade and you have to restart all instances of neutron-server.  There could be many of them.  At that point, *all* of them would be doing this sync process at the same time.

That's certainly not ideal, but I don't have a particularly good idea of something to suggest."}, {'account_id': 105, 'date': '2015-04-16 15:36:34.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

I agree with your concerns Russell, and they definitely seem valid. Also unsure how to work around that for now.

Other than that, this looks like a good direction to go in.'}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2015-04-16 15:44:07.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Maybe we could abuse an ovsdb lock for this.  I haven't looked at the Python API to see what's supported, but we could have a neutron-sync lock and only do the sync if the lock is acquired.  If the lock is already held (assuming we can request the lock and not block waiting for it), we could skip as a sync is already in progress."}, {'account_id': 11343, 'date': '2015-04-16 16:10:34.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Its important to mention here that if the DB's are synced no operation should be performed.
If i understood the IDL lib the action isn't really committed unless there is a change so your concern is only valid for changes.

The connection establishing is fetching the entire rows, so beside that i don't see any substantial load.

We should however consider how to establish a scale deployment, where we can benchmark and test various things not just for this issue.
Maybe ask for Justin help with that?"}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-04-16 16:10:35.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

Build succeeded (check pipeline).

- gate-networking-ovn-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/25/174425/1/check/gate-networking-ovn-pep8/9b7d63c/ : SUCCESS in 1m 40s
- gate-networking-ovn-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/25/174425/1/check/gate-networking-ovn-docs/41bb37f//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 1m 34s
- gate-networking-ovn-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/25/174425/1/check/gate-networking-ovn-python27/be99a6c/ : SUCCESS in 1m 48s
- check-tempest-dsvm-networking-ovn http://logs.openstack.org/25/174425/1/check/check-tempest-dsvm-networking-ovn/f324256/ : FAILURE in 13m 16s (non-voting)'}, {'account_id': 1561, 'date': '2015-04-16 16:15:35.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

It also has to load all of Neutron's resources from the neutron db, right?"}, {'account_id': 11343, 'date': '2015-04-16 16:27:32.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

yeah, any scripts / setups we can test that load?
(i can produce ones)

Anyway i forgot to add a file to this patch (utils.py), thats why its failing

Test2
--------
a. I terminated neutron server
b. i added few OVN port/network entries (using ovn-nbctl) with the external_ids' similar to neutron keys
c. Restarted neutron-server and checked that those entries are deleted

How about a config option like:

    [ovn]
    neutron_sync=[repair|log|off]

repair - During neutron-server startup, automatically create resources found in Neutron but not in OVN.  Also remove resources from OVN that are no longer in Neutron.

log - During neutron-server startup, check to see if OVN is in sync with the Neutron database.  Log warnings for any inconsistencies found so that an admin can investigate.

off - Do nothing.


With that, we could have the default policy as 'log'.  That seems pretty useful and can't really cause trouble."}, {'account_id': 11343, 'date': '2015-04-29 13:19:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6:

commit_message:
Add sync mechanism between neutron DB and OVN-NB DB

Sync all changed neutron objects to OVN-NB DB.
Remove from OVN-NB DB objects that are not found in neutron but
have neutron external ids

Change-Id: I7f0b0a728894f38006654e8d5f4599aec51af0c4
